1 AN ACT relating to interscholastic athletics.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 ïƒ¢Section 1. KRS 160.445 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) (a) The Kentucky Board of Education or organization or agency designated by
5 the board to manage interscholastic athletics shall require each interscholastic
6 coach to complete a sports safety course consisting of training on how to
7 prevent common injuries. The content of the course shall include but not be
8 limited to emergency planning, heat and cold illnesses, emergency
9 recognition, head injuries including concussions, neck injuries, facial injuries,
10 cardiopulmonary resuscitation, use of a portable automated external
11 defibrillator in accordance with KRS 311.667, [and ]principles of first aid,
12 and the psychological concerns in the student athlete. The course shall also
13 be focused on safety education and shall not include coaching principles.
14 (b) The state board or its agency shall:
15 1. Establish a minimum timeline for a coach to complete the course;
16 2. Approve providers of a sports safety course;
17 3. Be responsible for ensuring that an approved course is taught by
18 qualified professionals who shall either be athletic trainers, registered
19 nurses, physicians, or physician's assistants licensed to practice in
20 Kentucky;
21 4. Establish the minimum qualifying score for successful course
22 completion; and
23 5. Require a coach to earn a cardiopulmonary resuscitation certification
24 recognized by a national accrediting body on heart health.
25 (c) A course shall be reviewed for updates at least once every thirty (30) months
26 and revised if needed.
27 (d) A course shall be able to be completed through hands-on or online teaching
