1 practice or competition shall be removed from play at that time and shall not
2 return to play prior to the ending of the practice or competition until the
3 athlete is evaluated to determine if a concussion has occurred. The evaluation
4 shall be completed by a physician or a licensed health care provider whose
5 scope of practice and training includes the evaluation and management of
6 concussions and other brain injuries. A student athlete shall not return to play
7 on the date of a suspected concussion absent the required evaluation.
8 (b) 1. Upon completion of the required evaluation, a coach:
9 a. May return a student athlete to play if the physician or licensed
10 health care provider determines that no concussion has occurred;
11 or
12 b. Shall not return a student athlete to play if the physician or
13 licensed health care provider determines that a concussion has
14 occurred.
15 2. If no physician or licensed health care provider described in paragraph
16 (a) of this subsection is present at the practice or competition to perform
17 the required evaluation, a coach shall not return a student athlete to play
18 who is suspected of sustaining a concussion. The student athlete shall
19 not be allowed to participate in any subsequent practice or athletic
20 competition unless written clearance from a physician is provided.
21 (c) A student athlete deemed to be concussed shall not return to participate in any
22 athletic practice or competition occurring on the day of the injury. The injured
23 student athlete shall not be allowed to participate in any subsequent practice
24 or athletic competition unless written clearance from a physician is provided.
25 (4) The state board or its agency shall adopt rules governing interscholastic athletics
26 that encourage each school that participates in interscholastic athletics to provide
27 access to at least one (1) portable automated external defibrillator in a public,
