3 (5) The state board or its agency shall adopt rules governing interscholastic athletics
4 conducted by local boards of education to require each school that participates in
5 interscholastic athletics to develop a venue-specific emergency action plan to deal
6 with serious injuries and acute medical conditions in which the condition of the
7 patient may deteriorate rapidly. The plan shall:
8 (a) Include a delineation of the roles of staff and emergency personnel, methods
9 of communication, available emergency equipment, and access to and plan for
10 emergency transport;
11 (b) If one is available, identify the location of a portable automated external
12 defibrillator and the procedures for its use during an emergency; and
13 (c) Be in writing, reviewed by the principal of the school, distributed to all
14 appropriate personnel, posted conspicuously at all venues, and reviewed
15 annually and rehearsed by simulation prior to the beginning of each athletic
16 season by all:
17 1. Licensed athletic trainers, first responders, school nurses, athletic
18 directors; and
19 2. Interscholastic coaches and volunteer coaches of each athletic team
20 active during that athletic season.
21 (6) Each school shall submit annual written certification to the state board or its agency
22 of the existence of a venue-specific emergency action plan that the school has
23 reviewed and rehearsed by simulation as required by subsection (5)(c) of this
24 section.
25 (7) Each school shall maintain complete and accurate records of its compliance with
26 this section and shall make the records available for review by the state board or its
27 agency upon request.
